quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  27,14,They repudiated them wrongfully and haughtily though they themselves felt certain about it. See how the outcome was for mischief makers
  27,15,"We gave David and Solomon knowledge, and they both said: \"Praise be to God, Who has made us excel over many of His believing servants"
  27,16,"Solomon fell heir to David, and he said: \"O mankind, we have been taught the speech of birds, and been given [a little] of everything. This is manifest bounty"
  27,17,"His armies of sprites, men and birds were drawn up before Solomon; they paraded forth"
  27,18,"until, when they came to the Valley of the Ants, an ant said: \"O ants, enter your dwellings lest Solomon and his armies crush you without even noticing it"
  27,19,"So he smiled, laughing at its statement, and said: \"My Lord, arrange things for me so I shall act grateful for Your favor which You have bestowed upon me and my parents, and so I may act so honorably that You will approve of it. Admit me through Your mercy among Your honorable servants"
  27,20,"He inspected the birds, and said: \"WhatÂ´s wrong with me that I do not see the plover? Or could it be absent"
  27,21,"I shall punish it severely or slaughter it, unless it brings me some clear authority"
  27,22,"It was not long in coming, and said: \"I have just acquired some information you have not picked up, for I bring you reliable news from Sheba"